column5: Wow, only 51 and Gandolfini has died. They are saying a possible heart attack. A great example for reasons to keep in good physical shape and shed those extra pounds. Of course the details aren't fully out yet but When a still young person dies of a heart attack and they are overweight it sure seems like a waste. Anyway, RIP http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/19/showbiz/james-gandolfini-obituary/index.html
Sad news. His portrayal of Tony was epic. Rest In Peace James.
" they say you don't see it coming, it just goes black".   That show changed tv forever
A talented man gone. his acting skills were epic.
You beat me to it,  good. Actor.
A true legend in mob cinema.  RIP
Sad news. Great show.  As for   My last production manager was a fit man. Biked,run and worked out. Had a heart attack at the age of 40. He recovered,,It can happen to anyone.
I was surprised to learn that he was so young.  I thought he was at least 10 years older.
I thought at least 60. He's a year younger than me.Unbelieveable,so sad.
